President Biden has declared a major disaster in the State of Tennessee due to severe storms and straight-line winds that occurred from July 18 to July 21, 2023. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in Fayette, Henry, Shelby, and Tipton counties. Additionally, federal funding will be available for hazard mitigation measures statewide. Yolanda J. Jackson of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and more designations may be made if requested by the state and warranted by further damage assessments. For more information, media should contact the FEMA News Desk.